---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Newsletter — Simon Plant" description="Subscribe to get long-form writing on AI agent infrastructure, operational patterns, and the systems layer that makes agents production-ready.">
  <main class="section-spacing">
    <div class="container-prose">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-text-primary leading-tight mb-6">
        The infrastructure layer,<br />
        <span class="text-primary-400">delivered.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-[600px]">
        Long-form writing on AI agent infrastructure — lifecycle management, security hardening, operational patterns, and the systems thinking that turns demos into production. No hype, no filler. Just the work.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-surface-card border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6 md:p-8 mb-12 max-w-[600px]">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary mb-4">What you'll get</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-secondary mb-6 list-none p-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#9670;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-text-primary">Series installments</strong> — deep dives on agent infrastructure maturation, from provisioning to governance. 1,500–3,000 words, published biweekly.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#9670;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-text-primary">Commentary</strong> — short, opinionated takes on what's happening in AI infrastructure. When something worth writing about happens, you'll hear about it.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#9670;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-text-primary">Architecture patterns</strong> — structured records from real production decisions. Problems, trade-offs, and when to use what.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <form
          action="#"
          method="POST"
          class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3"
        >
          <label for="email" class="sr-only">Email address</label>
          <input
            id="email"
            name="email"
            type="email"
            required
            autocomplete="email"
            placeholder="you@example.com"
            class="flex-1 px-4 py-3 bg-surface-elevated border border-border-default rounded-md text-text-primary placeholder:text-text-muted focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-400/50 focus:border-primary-400 transition-colors"
          />
          <button
            type="submit"
            class="px-6 py-3 bg-primary-400 text-surface-bg font-semibold rounded-md hover:bg-primary-300 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-400/50 transition-colors cursor-pointer whitespace-nowrap"
          >
            Subscribe
          </button>
        </form>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mt-3">
          No spam. Unsubscribe anytime. Newsletter provider coming soon — sign up to be notified when it launches.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-t border-border-subtle pt-8">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary mb-4">Prefer RSS?</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
          All series and commentary are available via the <a href="/rss.xml" class="text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300 underline transition-colors">RSS feed</a>. Add it to your reader of choice — no account required.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
